      <title>Statistics | Simpson&#39;s Paradox</title>
      <link href="/Statistics-SimpsonParadox.html"/>
      <url>/Statistics-SimpsonParadox.html</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="Definition-定义"><a href="#Definition-定义" class="headerlink" title="Definition 定义"></a>Definition 定义</h2><p>辛普森悖论（Simpson’s Paradox）是概率和统计中的一种现象——两组数据分别观察时都具有某种性质，但合并到一起后性质消失或相反。</p><h2 id="References-参考"><a href="#References-参考" class="headerlink" title="References 参考"></a>References 参考</h2><ul><li>Simpson, E. H. (1951). <a href="https://rss.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.2517-6161.1951.tb00088.x"><strong>The interpretation of interaction in contingency tables</strong></a>. Journal of the Royal Statistical Society: Series B (Methodological), 13(2), 238-241.</li></ul>]]></content>
      
      
